mod-install.sh:

this script will attempt to install all the required perl modules
for pacpl.  For some it may be necessary to actually start the CPAN shell:

perl -MCPAN -e 'shell'

and from there type: install Module::Name

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
pacpl-gui.kmdr:

Kommander interface for pacpl.  

use: 'kmdr-executor pacpl-gui.kmdr' to run.  keep in mind that Kommander
must be installed in order to use this interface.

